article.description: Courtney Sims scored 21 points and Lester Abram added a season-high 14, leading Michigan to a 67-52 victory over Northern Illinois on Saturday.
article.headline: Michigan off to 11-1 start after coasting past No. Illinois
article.linkText: Michigan off to 11-1 start after coasting past No. Illinois
article.story: ANN ARBOR, Mich. (AP) -- Courtney Sims scored 21 points and Lester Abram added a season-high 14, leading Michigan to a 67-52 victory over Northern Illinois on Saturday. Sims, who also had 13 rebounds and three blocks, sparked the Wolverines (11-1) in the second half when Michigan led by as many as 19. Following a lackluster start, Michigan led 33-23 at the half. Sims scored nine of his points in the first half when Wolverines coach Tommy Amaker made wholesale line-up changes on three occasions. Michigan's reserves, led by Ekpe Udoh, maintained a slim lead during their first stint before Sims and his fellow starters extended the cushion by halftime. Northern Illinois (3-5), which led by as many as four early, was unable to slow down Michigan's athleticism or contend with its size. James Hughes and Zach Pancratz each scored 12 to lead the Huskies The Huskies got within six points early in the second half before Abram scored six straight Michigan points to again provide the Wolverines with a double-digit lead.
